********************************* ^xFFFF77^7^xFFFF77Should you play this build?^xFFFF77 ^7^xFFFF77^7******************************************
^x70FF70Pros:^7 - Adaptability -> Energyblade skeleton can make almost any spell good (obviously skills are not created equal, some are just better than others but who cares, play what you think is fun) - VERY strong intially on about 5-10d of gear with amazing scalability with each upgrading making a meaningful difference
^xE05030Cons:^7 - Has to Play Coruscating Elixir until much more min-maxed gear which allows dropping ivory/coruscating which is a QoL downside - Has a decent amount of map mods that are auto skips -> example: less defence(t17) / remove 5% life on hit(pk mod for lowlife builds, can run this after swapping out of coruscating) - Only had enough time to do some brief testing for early map progression so haven't 100% mapped out if staying EO till ivory swap vs crit is correct
^xAF6025^x8888FFSidenote:^7^7 - this type of character will make future characters feel weak (example: most spell skills will feel bad playing a different way after because scaling is just worse than eblade + battlemage inquis)
********************************* ^xFFFF77Skill Gem Setups to Try on build ^7******************************************
^x8888FF^xADAA47Self Cast Options^7: *Flameblast Celerity(this skill is just giga fun aoe clear + decent damage) *Incinerate of Venting(probably strongest single target, feels bad ramp until good gear, check out onemanaleft for an endgame example) *Penance Brand of Dissipation(one of the strongest self cast+mobility skills, requires picking up some brand stuff / explode for clear) *Wave of Conviction of Trathus(bit of an unknown but if running less duration allows consistent double hit seems like a great spell echo skill) depends on how duration + double hit stuff works ^xADAA47CoC Options^7: ^7*Eye of Winter BiS Single Target *Ice Spear of Splitting + Return Proj(BiS Clear with decent single target) *Bladefall(requires awakened cascade) Good Clear/Single Target *Blazing Salvo (use return) Good All Rounder ^xADAA47Mine Options^7: ^7*Ball Lightning of Orbiting All rounder Clear / Decent Single Target ^7*Eye of Winter Generally BiS Single Target with decent enough clear ^7*Arc Regular/Oscillating(potentially best feeling clearspeed with ok damage) *Frostblink Wintry Blast Theoretically good (requires aoe investment & solving chill proc)
^x70FF70IMPORTANT^7: Quality on Energy blade = 10% more es(10% more damage), with enhance =20% more es/damage, prioritize quality on this first, then other gems(IE if lab font gives you good quality then put it on EB)
********************************* ^xFFFF77Leveling ^7******************************************
^x70FF704hr Act 10 Eblade Run:^7 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ymCCfyB30qI
Vendor Regex(use in act 1/2): -\w-.-|b-b|g-r|r-g|nne|rint|Flam|Earn
^x70FF70This tree^7 was based on doing a straight into ^x7070FFEblade^7 right at lvl 30ish or so on first lab, if you don't want to do that a more basic firebased cast inquis leveling works fine just make sure you have gold/respecs to change when needed
^x70FF70First Lab = Battlemage^7: Battlemage + Energy/blade is just fairly solid damage early on, make sure to be picking up ES / hybrid ES pieces where you can to help this flat damage. If you find a very high ele damage one hand you can also use that and wait on using Eblade.

********************************* ^xFFFF77Mana ^7****************************************** ^x70FF70 Mana Solutions to aim for early: ^715% skill cost as mana as first life mastery / Mana Nodes ^x70FF70Mana Solutions to aim for in later setups:^7 Late game solution -> blood magic + eternal youth (sometimes life recharge turns off in predicitive mod, this is a bug with internet, swap to lockstep should help avoid this) ^x70FF70Mana Solutions for GIGA late game^7: Use unleveled skill where gem level doesn't change %effectiveness + high int/str investment gives a lot of base mana + Sanctuary of thought 50%ish more regen for mana
^xE05030Eternal Youth DOWNSIDE^7: There are a select few mechanics in poe that turn off recovery, Exarch ground(i think not 100% sure)/Sirus Ground/Maven Degen beam if you get hit by or stand in one of these the life recharge will be deactivated for 2+ seconds thus softlocking skill use for a bit. Simply Avoid Sirus/exarch Ground mod on T17s & you have to play around those mechanics in ubers, very doable(sirus is the only real problematic one imo)
********************************* ^xFFFF77Eternal Youth BUG ^7******************************************
sometimes life recharge turns off in predicitive mod, this is a bug with internet, swap to lockstep should help avoid this but it happens on occasion to people based on what people have told me, I've run into this issue a few times but its very rare and generally for most people predictive fixes the issue
********************************* ^xFFFF77Snacks ^7******************************************
^x70FF70S-Tier:^7 Water(only drink you will ever need) Doughnuts(best snacking desert there is) Eggs -> scrambled/omelet/breakfast sandwich combo, always good no matter how you make em
^x70FF70A-Tier:^7 Cereal -> time efficient breakfast to get gaming faster(i recommend granola) Dino Nuggies(fairly time efficient, we can pretend its meal) (pair with mac-cheese) Frozen Pizza(fairly time efficient also kindof technically a meal) Taquitos(idk how good these are, but chat seems to love and won't shut up about it) Mac-Cheese = Easy/Time Efficient we can pretend this is almost a meal (pair with dino nuggies) Club Crackers solid snack easy and affordable Gold fish (i'd put this in S-tier if my babies had more control of this list) Oreos/Preffered Cookie + Milk (pretty min-max for taste value but does require setup of milk & oreos -1 minute efficiency) Milk/Protein Shake-> delicious/filling -> requires a blender Peanuts the most notable nut there is, personally i like honey roasted but you do you Potatoes -> great build diversity, can min-max into basically any meal (do not consume raw) Cheeze-itz(previously S, moved down due to lack of it being in my pantry recently) Popeyes(been on a popeyes kick recently and I am biased)
^x70FF70B-Tier:^7 Asiago Bagels + cream cheese (decently time efficient but mid risk of cream cheesing your keyboard) Ice Cream(bit less time efficient but tastes amazing, i recommend peanut butter + vanilla ice cream + dark choco chips that you keep in freezer) Fruit snacks (easy & convenient) but will screw your teeth Smoothie(dealers choice of ingredients) decent setup time, not a tasty as a shake probably healthier Pretzels maximize water efficiency and help you pretend you aren't starving from lack of real food (add in whipped creamed cheese and it goes to A-tier) Cashews Delicious and a bit more cost efficient than pistachios Tea bit of setup time with boiling water but fantastically soothing Chipotle -> delicious but super costly if you pay to deliver OR you brick your time efficiency by going to store Eggo Waffles -> pretty solid time efficiency, charlotte loves these Quesadilla -> cost efficient & easy to make solid flavor Chips & Salsa (not my thing but a staple classic for many, just don't spill the salsa) +add guac for 10 points of flavor but -10 in time it takes to mash up the avocado Oatmeal -> pretty filling, results in high end gaming, not BiS flavour but gets the job done
^x70FF70C-Tier:^7 Hotdogs Fairly time efficient, quality will vary greatly depending on what dogs you get and how you cook them (F tier= microwave, A tier if grilled with high quality dogs) Pistachios super tasty but kinda p2w nut Honey Buns -> tasty unhealthy fast & you will need to wash hands Beef Jerky (mid taste in my opinion but if thats your thing it could jump up some tiers due to time efficiency/ease) Gummy Bears -> solid but will get stuck to teeth which feels bad Grilled Cheese Decent time consumption, high flavor, can vary greatly on how its made
^x70FF70D-Tier:^7 Hot-Pocket(time efficient, seem way worse than I remember)(will probably burn your tongue) Cheetos/Doritos => tasty snakc but finger debuff will destroy your keyboard/efficiency Reese's -> RIP teeth Skittles -> RIP teeth Star Burst -> RIP teeth
^x70FF70F-Tier:^7 Popcorn -> thing will get stuck in teeth, GG - multiple hours due to pure tilt and efficiency loss Every other drink known to mankind (bud light) raisins -> just a creeper version of a grape BabyCarrots/Cucumbers w/ humus(too healthy, almost like you know what the sun looks like) Poptarts super time efficient but you will feel dirty on the inside eating them & they kinda suck now Apples Pokimane Cookies(you disappoint me) Door-Dash -> giga expensive, could have gotten a new pc
********************************* ^xFFFF77The End ^7******************************************
